103 111 moveto (Expressions of Class Type) show
55 execuserobject setfont
6 157 moveto (A previous paper by Tom Plum and Scott Turner  \( N0293 / 93-0086 \)  discussed the  
lvalue-ness of) show
6 170 moveto (temporaries.    The original paper noted a number of consequences of deciding that these  
expressions) show
6 183 moveto (are lvalues, const lvalues, or non-lvalues \( assuming the C model\).  The only real decision  
made was that) show
6 196 moveto (they were not completely lvalues.  The result was a vote by the committee that these constucts  
were not) show
6 209 moveto ("lvalues"  but in some sense refered to objects.  \( N0306 /  93-0099 \).) show
6 235 moveto (Since then much discussion has been seen on the core reflector.  It is evident that there are two  
schools) show
6 248 moveto (of thougth.  Some want such objects to be first class objects in all sense of the word, and  
behave much) show
6 261 moveto (more like lvalues.  I will refer to this school of thought as like lvalues or LLV.  Others want these  
objects) show
6 274 moveto (to behave much more like C built in types and be totally value oriented.  This school I will refer  
to as the) show
6 287 moveto (abstract data types, or ADT.   I took some info from the net and some in conversations from  
Kent Budge,) show
6 300 moveto (but this is a synthesis of how I think the ADT camp wants things.  Furthermore,  I will  
shamelessly steal) show
6 313 moveto (from the original paper in format and analysis and call such constructor or function expressions  
CI expr.) show
