6 2285 moveto (Adopt the strategy described  in the above examples) show
6 2311 moveto (First,  declare that CV qualifiers on return types are meaningful.   The CV qualifier takes effect  
after the) show
6 2324 moveto (value has been created \(from the functions return expression\).   This is similar to the effect of  
CV) show
6 2337 moveto (qualifiers for function arguments.  They affect the value after it has been copied or  
constructed.) show
6 2363 moveto (Fix overloading  for  member functions.  Define the bahavior to work similar to how Cfront does  
now.) show
6 2376 moveto (That is:  A temporary of  class type const T binds only to const member functions.  A  
termporary of type T) show
6 2389 moveto (binds to either const or non-const member functions but prefers non-const.) show
6 2415 moveto (For function argument overloading, use the same selection mechanism.   Non-qualified  
returns of class) show
6 2428 moveto (type would prefer binding to non const references.  Const qualified returns would only bind to  
const) show
6 2441 moveto (references.  Note that matching for value type arguments are dependent only on the  
constructors) show
6 2454 moveto (accessible \(see section below\).) show
6 2480 moveto (The effect of these changes are that the objects returned by functions returning class objects  
and) show
6 2493 moveto (constructor expressions, are in all ways lvalues except fot the explicit taking of address \(built  
in &\).) show
6 2506 moveto (Examples have shown this is already the case, since any function that binds to a class type  
object can) show
6 2519 moveto (take an address.) show
